101
00:05:49.360 --> 00:05:52.780
HPV vaccines are based on L1 virus-like particles, which

102
00:05:52.900 --> 00:05:56.860
spontaneously assemble and mimic authentic virus capsid,

103
00:05:56.940 --> 00:06:00.480
which induces high titer virion neutralizing antibodies.

104
00:06:00.520 --> 00:06:04.252
These are both non-infectious and non-oncogenic.The

105
00:06:04.272 --> 00:06:08.152
vaccines were initially approved in 2006 as a three-dose regimen

106
00:06:08.232 --> 00:06:12.092
based on clinical trial data. The HPV vaccine does

107
00:06:12.212 --> 00:06:15.972
prevent infections at all the anatomic sites where HPV causes

108
00:06:16.092 --> 00:06:19.352
cancer. We do know this from clinical trial data, both

109
00:06:19.472 --> 00:06:21.452
randomized and observational.

110
00:06:22.452 --> 00:06:26.012
Real-world data shows a 90% reduction in cervical

111
00:06:26.022 --> 00:06:29.782
pre-cancer and cancer among women vaccinated as adolescents.

112
00:06:30.372 --> 00:06:34.332
Vaccination is easier than cervical cancer screening, though we have to acknowledge

113
00:06:34.402 --> 00:06:38.012
that screening remains critically important because it brings

114
00:06:38.052 --> 00:06:40.622
faster reductions in cervical cancer incidence.

115
00:06:41.062 --> 00:06:43.802
So vaccination is an investment in our future.

116
00:06:43.812 --> 00:06:47.372
Cervical cancer screening cuts out the prevalent disease in the

117
00:06:47.412 --> 00:06:51.032
moment. There is no population-based screening for HPV-driven

118
00:06:51.092 --> 00:06:54.062
cancers out beyond the cervix. So what's the problem?

119
00:06:54.062 --> 00:06:57.692
I just told you all this great news. Like, it works. Let's celebrate.

120
00:06:58.152 --> 00:06:59.432
Well, around 2020,

121
00:07:00.252 --> 00:07:04.162
which was 15, 16, 17 years after the initial recommendations of

122
